content.description: Sit start (on the left center of the east face) on a positive rail and move up to a positive hold. From there, move right using small crimps and delicate feet.
content.protection: Pads and a spotter. There are a few small rocks under the landing and a larger one behind, but a pad will nearly fit between it and the prolem.
content.location:
The route starts on the positive rail in the left-center of the east face. It starts in the same place as

Bloody Knuckles

but from there moves right and up.

The downclimb is on the northwest corner using the tree and the boulder to shimmy down.

content.description: Sit start with a low left hand edge and a right hand stacked above on an awkward two-finger pocket. From there, gain a left hand edge, follow to a right hand incut edge, reach and match on the edge above, and mantel atop the boulder.
content.protection: A pair of pads. The immediate landing is good, but there is a large rock behind the problem.
content.location: It climbs the west face of Jason vs. Freddy.

content.description: Sit start matched on obvious edge. From there, gain a sloping left hand sidepull, follow to a right hand undercling-sidepull, gain an edge, follow to the lip, and mantel on top.
content.protection: A pad or two. The landing is good.
content.location: It climbs the center of Jason vs. Freddy's west face.

content.description: Sit start with a left hand on the arete and a right hand jug. From there, bump up the arete, and use face edges with the right to reach an easy mantel.
content.protection: A pad or two. The landing is good.
content.location: It climbs the west face of Jason vs. Freddy.

content.description: Sit start matched on a vertical feature. From there, follow the north side of the arete to the lip and eventual beached whale topout.
content.protection: A pad or two. The landing is good, but there is a rock and tree just outside the fall zone.
content.location: It climbs the north side of Jason vs. Freddy's northeast arete.

content.description: Sit start on the southwest arete. Move up and slightly around the arete and top out. The crux is slapping up the arete to the big jug, and it's easy after that. This will get better with traffic as lichen will be removed.
content.location: The problem is on the southwest arete. There's a downclimb via a juniper tree/boulder to get down.

content.description: Sit start on a pair of small crimps and feet on the right hand side. Make a crux move to a positive hold, match, and make a big move up to the jug. Top out.
content.location: This is located on the south end of the east face. Downclimb via a tree and the boulder on the north side.
